commit.message:
Split tape codec out of CapnCpp so bundles can tree-shake it

The capnweb-shape serialize/deserialize methods on CapnCpp dragged
tape_codec.mjs into every bundle that touched the loader, even RPC-only
clients that never call them. Promote them to free functions in
js/tape_serializer.mjs (re-exported as `capnwasm/tape`):

  // before
  import { CapnCpp } from "capnwasm";
  cpp.serialize(value);

  // after
  import { CapnCpp } from "capnwasm";
  import { serialize } from "capnwasm/tape";
  serialize(cpp, value);

Inlined bundles also stop concatenating tape_codec since `load()` no
longer references it. Result:

  inlined.slim.mjs:    64 KB → 61 KB gzip   (58 KB brotli)
  inlined.mjs:         71 KB → 69 KB gzip   (64 KB brotli)
  capnwasm/browser:                45 KB gzip   (42 KB brotli)

bench/run-in-browser.mjs is the only internal caller; updated to use
the free-function form. tape_codec.mjs and TapeWriter/TapeReader are
unchanged and still re-exported from the main entrypoint.
